# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: VargaMarionPath | Scene: VargaPath2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The council meeting was over and the room was empty, save for Sarah and Thomas."
    new "The council meeting was over and the room was empty, save for Sarah and Thomas."

    old "Thomas sat not in his chair, but balanced on the edge of the table."
    new "Thomas sat not in his chair, but balanced on the edge of the table."

    old "The news of Sarah and Varga's enagement had spread like wildfire, and with a few days past, by now most of the kingdom knew."
    new "The news of Sarah and Varga's enagement had spread like wildfire, and with a few days past, by now most of the kingdom knew."

    old "With so much work to do, the siblings had had little privacy until today."
    new "With so much work to do, the siblings had had little privacy until today."

    old "Sarah, you know that officially, you need my blessing for the marriage."
    new "Sarah, you know that officially, you need my blessing for the marriage."

    old "Sarah knew this was true, but had given it little thought."
    new "Sarah knew this was true, but had given it little thought."

    old "But I imagine that's little more than a formality, right?"
    new "But I imagine that's little more than a formality, right?"

    old "It is. You can marry anyone you want, you know that. I'd never object. It's just, you know, I would only want to know that you were happy."
    new "It is. You can marry anyone you want, you know that. I'd never object. It's just, you know, I would only want to know that you were happy."

    old "It's kind of you to worry about me Thomas, but as the older sister, that should really be my job."
    new "It's kind of you to worry about me Thomas, but as the older sister, that should really be my job."

    old "Sarah sat down on the edge of the table next to Thomas."
    new "Sarah sat down on the edge of the table next to Thomas."

    old "And in case you wonder, he does make me happy."
    new "And in case you wonder, he does make me happy."

    old "Sarah let her eyes roll back, staring at the ceiling."
    new "Sarah let her eyes roll back, staring at the ceiling."

    old "Gods was it true, he made her so happy."
    new "Gods was it true, he made her so happy."

    old "Sarah had feared that the engagement would be like a high point in their new relationship, with everything after feeling dull by comparison, but the opposite had happened."
    new "Sarah had feared that the engagement would be like a high point in their new relationship, with everything after feeling dull by comparison, but the opposite had happened."

    old "Following their official engagement, the two lovers had found themselves with more flexibility."
    new "Following their official engagement, the two lovers had found themselves with more flexibility."

    old "They were could be alone more, people raised fewer questions and rumors, and they found more opportunities to be together."
    new "They were could be alone more, people raised fewer questions and rumors, and they found more opportunities to be together."

    old "And in this new stage, the two began to explore one another."
    new "And in this new stage, the two began to explore one another."

    old "The physical side was frozen for the moment, each agreeing to hold off until the wedding, but Sarah had found herself surprised that she was almost as eager to learn of the man as his body."
    new "The physical side was frozen for the moment, each agreeing to hold off until the wedding, but Sarah had found herself surprised that she was almost as eager to learn of the man as his body."

    old "Varga had told her more of his upbringing, the staggering poverty of his family. To Sarah, it seemed hard to imagine, and she found herself weeping for the plight of people she never met."
    new "Varga had told her more of his upbringing, the staggering poverty of his family. To Sarah, it seemed hard to imagine, and she found herself weeping for the plight of people she never met."

    old "But he also told her about the beauty that existed even in poverty."
    new "But he also told her about the beauty that existed even in poverty."

    old "The way he could describe the rolling fields in summer, oceans of wheat dancing to the breeze, it made Sarah want to escape the castle and travel the country with him."
    new "The way he could describe the rolling fields in summer, oceans of wheat dancing to the breeze, it made Sarah want to escape the castle and travel the country with him."

    old "As he opened up to her, she felt the desire to reciprocate."
    new "As he opened up to her, she felt the desire to reciprocate."

    old "Surprising even herself, one day alone in the gardens, Sarah had shared the memories she had of her mother with Varga."
    new "Surprising even herself, one day alone in the gardens, Sarah had shared the memories she had of her mother with Varga."

    old "She had spoken of those with nobody, not even Thomas."
    new "She had spoken of those with nobody, not even Thomas."

    old "All her life she had kept them inside of herselves, fearing that if she spoke them out loud, they might become susceptible to the erosion of the real world."
    new "All her life she had kept them inside of herselves, fearing that if she spoke them out loud, they might become susceptible to the erosion of the real world."

    old "Instead, she found it to be the opposite. Now she knew the memories of her mother lived on in her, as they did in Varga."
    new "Instead, she found it to be the opposite. Now she knew the memories of her mother lived on in her, as they did in Varga."

    old "To love his man, she had come to learn, was a joy that eclipsed any other she had known."
    new "To love his man, she had come to learn, was a joy that eclipsed any other she had known."

    old "In the deep nights, when she felt the emptiness of her bed and worried, she whispered the words 'husband and wife', and like a spell, they warmed her."
    new "In the deep nights, when she felt the emptiness of her bed and worried, she whispered the words 'husband and wife', and like a spell, they warmed her."

    old "Little did Sarah know that Varga whispered the same spell in his bed most evenings."
    new "Little did Sarah know that Varga whispered the same spell in his bed most evenings."

    old "Thomas stood up and turned to face Sarah."
    new "Thomas stood up and turned to face Sarah."

    old "Then I just want you to know that I'll give you my blessing, Sarah. Always."
    new "Then I just want you to know that I'll give you my blessing, Sarah. Always."

    old "Sarah smiled at her brother. She had never doubted he would grant his blessing, and yet, hearing him say it still moved her heart."
    new "Sarah smiled at her brother. She had never doubted he would grant his blessing, and yet, hearing him say it still moved her heart."

    old "You should have seen the nobles, lined out the door begging me to forbid the marriage."
    new "You should have seen the nobles, lined out the door begging me to forbid the marriage."

    old "I bet they all had their little designs. Serves them right, always creeping and plotting in the shadows."
    new "I bet they all had their little designs. Serves them right, always creeping and plotting in the shadows."

    old "Sarah wished she could say she was surprised at this, but she too had heard the rumors."
    new "Sarah wished she could say she was surprised at this, but she too had heard the rumors."

    old "And there was a truth to them. Matches between the Rose family were exclusively sourced from the old houses, or on rare exception, a noble house with great standing."
    new "And there was a truth to them. Matches between the Rose family were exclusively sourced from the old houses, or on rare exception, a noble house with great standing."

    old "For her to marry an upstart, a newly made noble, who himself had lived as a commoner once..."
    new "For her to marry an upstart, a newly made noble, who himself had lived as a commoner once..."

    old "Sarah tried to remember her history, recalling if ever such a thing had happened, but she couldn't remember a single instance."
    new "Sarah tried to remember her history, recalling if ever such a thing had happened, but she couldn't remember a single instance."

    old "Thank you for standing up for me, Thomas. I know it isn't easy."
    new "Thank you for standing up for me, Thomas. I know it isn't easy."

    old "I'd be lying if I said I didn't enjoy watching them squirm just a little. But I do think I'll have to come up with a way to fix the bridges you've burned."
    new "I'd be lying if I said I didn't enjoy watching them squirm just a little. But I do think I'll have to come up with a way to fix the bridges you've burned."

    old "Marion, especially. I mean, I know you didn't speak of it, nor did I, but someone did."
    new "Marion, especially. I mean, I know you didn't speak of it, nor did I, but someone did."

    old "Everyone will deny they heard the story, but by now it's the hottest piece of gossip in the capital, probably the nation."
    new "Everyone will deny they heard the story, but by now it's the hottest piece of gossip in the capital, probably the nation."

    old "I overhead someone telling the story, and in that version, you knocked him unconscious."
    new "I overhead someone telling the story, and in that version, you knocked him unconscious."

    old "Sarah struggled to see the humor in it. But Thomas wasn't entirely wrong. She had been right to be angry, but she might have gone too far."
    new "Sarah struggled to see the humor in it. But Thomas wasn't entirely wrong. She had been right to be angry, but she might have gone too far."

    old "You're right though, Thomas. I should have thought more before I did what I did. I just got so angry..."
    new "You're right though, Thomas. I should have thought more before I did what I did. I just got so angry..."

    old "It's so unlike me to let myself be carried away, but when he did that...I just lost it."
    new "It's so unlike me to let myself be carried away, but when he did that...I just lost it."

    old "Thomas gave his sister a soft punch on her arm, hoping to get her to lighten up."
    new "Thomas gave his sister a soft punch on her arm, hoping to get her to lighten up."

    old "Like I said, Sarah, it will work itself out. Marion can sulk, and I'll throw him a feast or a maybe gift him some new fancy title."
    new "Like I said, Sarah, it will work itself out. Marion can sulk, and I'll throw him a feast or a maybe gift him some new fancy title."

    old "We'll all pretend it never happened, happy ever after."
    new "We'll all pretend it never happened, happy ever after."

    old "Sarah and Thomas carried on their conversation."
    new "Sarah and Thomas carried on their conversation."

    old "Until late in the day, Sarah spoke to Thomas about Varga."
    new "Until late in the day, Sarah spoke to Thomas about Varga."

    old "Whatever doubt about the match might have resided in her brother's consideration, vanished."
    new "Whatever doubt about the match might have resided in her brother's consideration, vanished."

